main event: On July 17, 1963, a sighting of a space vehicle was reported in Spencer, West Virginia, lasting approximately 10 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed traveling in a northeast or east-northeast direction,The observation was completely visual without any photographs taken,The object was described as possibly being a satellite,The case was initially considered for identification as a satellite or other known objects by the USAF,There is uncertainty regarding the true nature of the object observed due to lack of confirmation or additional information.
witness description: A person reported observing the object but further details were not provided.
